	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That's my guess too when I first saw it. It would be very useful on a board with sockets to have a switch to select H/V mirroring. Alot easier than having two seperate boards for horizontal and vertical scrolling games. The guess is reinforced by the lack of any memory mapper on the board. 
<br />
<br />If the game scrolls, having the switch in the opposite position should make the scrolling messed up.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
